---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_output(& [\"lint\", \"--help\"])"
---
Report lint violations across the project

Runs each language's linter and prints normalized diagnostics (file:line:col, rule, message), exiting 1 when any remain. --fix applies safe autofixes first, then reports what is left; --format json emits a stable, machine-readable schema.

Usage: hpds lint [OPTIONS] [PATHS]...

Arguments:
  [PATHS]...
          Files or directories to lint (default: the whole project)

Options:
      --fix
          Apply safe autofixes first, then report what remains

  -v, --verbose
          Show more detail (underlying commands, tool names)

      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format
          
          [default: text]
          [possible values: text, json]

  -q, --quiet
          Suppress all output except errors

      --no-color
          Disable colored output

      --config <PATH>
          Use this config file instead of discovering hpds.toml

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
